Hey sorry for getting back so late, I decided the simple inbox/outbox was good enough for me.

Regarding that I faced a strange/interesting issue, which is I could send data from BSC Testnet to Mumbai but not the other way around. I'm wondering is it maybe to do with how I'm handling the domain identifier in ethers.js? My code looks something like this:

const domainId = 80001;
const targetContractAddress = '0x...';
const someRandomData = '....';
const contract = await ethers.getContract('MyContract');
contract.send(domainId, targetContractAddress, someRandomData);

The contract's send method is really simple, it does some simple stuff before forwarding the data on the the Outbox's dispatch method. It all works fine but when domainId is instead assigned to the documented BSC value of 0x62732d74 (needless to say I also change the targetContractAddress accordingly), the transaction goes through but I never ever receive the message on the destination contract.

Do you have any thoughts on maybe how I could be handling the BSC domain identifier number value starting with '0x' wrongly in ethers.js? Thanks!

